Comparing Four Measures of Codon Bias

Full set of genes: 1620 genes, each different at the nucleotide sequence level across 22 strains

Partial set of genes: 185 genes, each different at the nucleotide sequence level and identical at the amino acid sequence level across 22 strains

09/11/2019

library(car)
library(lme4)
library(reshape2)

Analysis of Codon Bias on the Full Set of Genes

Define the response variable.

response <- read.csv('n_PPR_1620_d.csv')
dataset <- melt(response, id.vars = "gene", variable.name = "strain", value.name = "PPR")
dataset$logPPR <- log(dataset$PPR)

Codon Adaptation Index (CAI) with Carbone Reference Set

Menu
Read in Data
explanatory1 <- read.csv('CAI_Carbone_1620_YRC_diff_d.csv')
explanatory1 <- melt(explanatory1, id.vars = "gene", variable.name = "strain", value.name = "CAI")
dataset$CAI <- explanatory1$CAI
Summary Results of Mixed Model
lmm1 <- lmer(logPPR ~ CAI + (1+CAI|gene), data=dataset, REML = FALSE, control = lmerControl(optimizer="bobyqa", optCtrl=list(maxfun=1e5)))
summary(lmm1)
## Linear mixed model fit by maximum likelihood  ['lmerMod']
## Formula: logPPR ~ CAI + (1 + CAI | gene)
##    Data: dataset
## Control: lmerControl(optimizer = "bobyqa", optCtrl = list(maxfun = 1e+05))
## 
##       AIC       BIC    logLik  deviance  df.resid 
## -105776.2 -105725.4   52894.1 -105788.2     35634 
## 
## Scaled residuals: 
##      Min       1Q   Median       3Q      Max 
## -18.3432  -0.3986   0.0248   0.4348  10.9702 
## 
## Random effects:
##  Groups   Name        Variance Std.Dev. Corr 
##  gene     (Intercept) 0.612543 0.78265       
##           CAI         2.274394 1.50811  -0.06
##  Residual             0.001991 0.04462       
## Number of obs: 35640, groups:  gene, 1620
## 
## Fixed effects:
##             Estimate Std. Error t value
## (Intercept)   7.5286     0.0267 281.939
## CAI           0.9029     0.1017   8.876
## 
## Correlation of Fixed Effects:
##     (Intr)
## CAI -0.641
Fixed Effects Slope Significance Results
lmm2 <- lmer(logPPR ~ (1+CAI|gene), data=dataset, REML = FALSE, control = lmerControl(optimizer="bobyqa", optCtrl=list(maxfun=1e5)))
anova(lmm1, lmm2)
## Data: dataset
## Models:
## lmm2: logPPR ~ (1 + CAI | gene)
## lmm1: logPPR ~ CAI + (1 + CAI | gene)
##      Df     AIC     BIC logLik deviance  Chisq Chi Df Pr(>Chisq)    
## lmm2  5 -105705 -105663  52858  -105715                             
## lmm1  6 -105776 -105725  52894  -105788 72.977      1  < 2.2e-16 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
Diagnostic Plots
par(mfrow=c(2,2))
res = residuals(lmm1)

scatter.smooth(fitted(lmm1), res, col='slateblue', span=0.1, xlab='Fitted Values', ylab='Residuals')
scatter.smooth(dataset$CAI, res, col='slateblue', span=0.1, xlab='CAI (Carbone)', ylab='Residuals')
qqnorm(res, col='slateblue')
qqline(res)
hist(res, main='', xlab='Residuals', ylab='Frequency', col='slateblue')
